    <stitle>Body Builder Electrical Data Book - SINGLE REDUCTION AXLES: SPICER S100-S, S105-S, S135-S, S150-S -
        IDENTIFICATION - GEAR SET
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>GEAR SET</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1401703">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1401703" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic id="g1401703" filename="../figg14/G1401703.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"
                     scalefitheight="352px"/>
            <caption>Figure 3. Gear Set Identification</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Manufacturer's date</emph>
            - date gear set was made.
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">360GP104</emph>
            - part number of pinion gear (typical).
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Tooth Combination (i.e., 41-11)</emph>
            - indicates the ring gear has 41 teeth and the pinion 11 teeth which results in a 3.73:1 ratio.
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Matched set number</emph>
            - Ring and pinions are manufactured as a matched set. Both pieces are marked with a corresponding number
            (i.e., 260) which identifies them as a matched set.
        </para>
        <para>A gear set that does not have the same matching numbers should not be mated together. If either a ring
            gear or pinion requires replacement,
            <emph type="bold">they must be replaced as a matched set</emph>.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
